node.text: President Joe Biden and House Speaker Nancy Pelosi recently voiced their support for California Gov. Gavin Newsom, who is facing a close recall election. Gov. Newsom has been heavily criticized for violating his own draconian COVID-19 restrictions and for not cracking down on the rising crime in the Golden State. California gubernatorial candidate Larry Elder will respond TONIGHT on “Hannity.”

node.text: Afghanistan is falling apart and the Taliban is making major advances, even conquering the country’s second and third largest cities. Now, the Biden administration is begging the Taliban to spare the U.S. Embassy in Kabul. Do they really think a radical terror group will listen to reason? In a recent op-ed, Rep. Michael Waltz, who served in Afghanistan, described how he thinks President Biden should handle the situation. Tune into “Hannity” TONIGHT at 9 PM ET or set your DVR to hear from Rep. Waltz!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sean Hannity on August 13, 2021. May be an image of ‎1 person and ‎text that says '‎CHICAGO IN CRISIS ۔ Hannity‎'‎‎.

node.text: Chicago Mayor Lori Lightfoot’s feud with the police in her city is back in the spotlight following the murder of Chicago police officer Ella French. Police officers at the University of Chicago Medical Center, where French’s partner remains in critical condition, turned their backs on Lightfoot in protest. How can a city stay safe when police and lawmakers are fighting? Chicago Alderman Raymond Lopez and former police officer Tre Pennie will weigh in TONIGHT on “Hannity.”

Former Energy Secretary Rick Perry will weigh in TONIGHT on “Hannity.”
